        "type": "text",
        "text": "Perfect! ✓ Your 7-segment counter is ready. \n\n**How it works:**\n- Press the button on pin 9 to increment the display\n- Counter goes 0 → 1 → 2 → ... → 9 → 0 → 1 ...\n- Each segment (a–g) has a 220Ω resistor to limit current\n- The display updates instantly with debouncing to prevent false counts\n\nThe sketch uses a lookup function that sets each segment HIGH/LOW based on the digit (0–9)."
